instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The framework defines a full DT life‑cycle anchored in BIM. It starts with device modeling by Building Control Engineers using Autodesk Revit custom families and property sets; each modeled device receives an Instance General UUID and an IFC‑type (e.g., IFCLIGHTFIXTURETYPE). The enriched BIM model is exported as IFC and passed through a dedicated IFC model checker that validates required metadata. In the next stage, the Semantic Model Extraction (F2) automatically derives a domain‑specific semantic model from the IFC file. A one‑click deployment (F3) then generates, configures and launches the DT artifacts, creating runtime instances that are linked to physical assets via Eclipse Hono/Ditto middleware (F4). During operation, live bidirectional data exchange (F4) and interactive 3‑D visualization (F5) keep the physical and digital twins synchronized. Runtime Configuration Management (F7) allows dynamic re‑configuration without redeployment, and modular service integration (F6) enables extension throughout the operational phase. Governance is realised through the roles defined in Table I (Building Control Engineer, Facility Manager, DT Engineer) that handle modeling, monitoring, and service extension respectively."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
